latestIgtvVideos.title: Two Product Washday with @reequil
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
➡️This simple wash day I have shared here is perfect for days when you want to be home or any day when your are not looking for a hold but want soft manageable curls. I do not recommend skipping on a leave in on any wash day. 
.
.
➡️ This is also a  perfect routine for beginners, when you don't want to indulge in buying a lot of products and still experimenting and learning. 
.
.
🌻 Please remember to hold your curls longer, you need a GEL. So you can follow up with a gel with the above routine if you are looking for hold. 
.
.
I absolutely love the @reequil conditioners and I highly recommend you to try these if you haven't done so yet. Even the shampoos are a great choice if you looking for strong one. Dandruff control is one of my favourites. It keeps my scalp calm till next wash day. You can use my code KHUSH for a 20% off on their website. 
.
.
➡️ Reequil Pea protein mask - I have used a tub of this one too. Its a decent deep conditioner. I feel it's more of a balanced one. I would have preferred if it was a little more moisturising. It gives me a decent protein effect. Slip is also fine but I had higher expectations after using thier conditioners. All in all its an average deep conditioner. 
.
.
For any other questions you may have drop them in the comments 😊
.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: STC using Bowl Method
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
*Squish to Condish using Bowl Method*
.
.
I use this technique only when my hair is getting too dry or when I am skipping my Deep Conditioning. The video is slightly long as I wanted to explain in detail. if you have any other doubts please leave them in comments below. 
.
.
Bowl Method was introduced to us by the gorgeous @powerdomi . Thank you for this amazing method. It's so helpful in so many ways.
.
.
Edit : To remove conditioner from above your neck add some water there using a spray bottle or as you are comfortable and scrunch it out. Alternatively you can give a final rinse to your hair by pouring water over it which will remove the excess conditioner, instead of 2nd or 3rd time repeating the process. 
.
.
You can use your favourite conditioner for STC. Here are the ones I love to use for it -

@letscurlupdotcom Conditioner
@vilvah_ Cream Conditioner
@bestlifenaturals argan nourish Conditioner. 
.
.
You can do the same using your favourite Deep conditioner too 😊.
.
.
The brush used here is from Miniso. you can find one in my Amazon storefront. link in Bio. 
.

What a fun event it was!! 
From seeing my scalp under a scanner to learning how Dove’s Scalp Therapy Serum helps grow up to 10,000 more hairs in upto 8 weeks* — this was a deep dive worth taking.
Because real hair care? Starts at the root.

*Based on clinical study, 2024 for usual hair thinning

#AD #DoveScalpTherapy #DoveSOS #ScalpCareIsSelfCare #HealthyHairStartsHere #HairGoals #ScalpLove #DovePartner #DoveIndia

I am back !! Hello My Insta Fam 💖 !! 

I know I have been away for very long. It was a little difficult time for my family and me in April and most of May as one of the most important person in our family had to undergo a very major surgery. When we learnt about it in April it was really difficult to absorb. I was completely shaken, lost and sad from inside. I tried my best to look my normal self on the outside but I felt really lost. Insta took a complete back seat for me. I only continued doing the essential things. 

With Gods blessings the surgery went well. It’s a long road to recovery but I am glad the most difficult part is over. I got back to Goa on 18th May but was just finding it difficult to get back to Insta. Have been thinking of doing so everyday but somehow couldn’t. But here I am all ready and set. I will be honest I really missed being here and these long breaks are worst for my account too, I know. But the over emotional I am, my family has always come first for me. Before anything else in the world. Even a small discomfort to them puts me completely off and this was the most major ever. With all my heart I hope and pray no one have to go through these tough times but I guess this is life and we all have to live through. 

Love and lots of love to you all 💖 How have you guys been ?? Missed me ??

Not that’s it’s a big thing but after hating your curls for years when you start loving them it’s really different. The day I actually styled them for the first time after this long break it just felt so amazing I can’t explain. .

#curlyhair #frizzyhair #curlyhairtips #hairwash #curlstyling #haircaretips

Comment “flyaway” if you need the link for these directly in your DMs

The wax stick is from @moxiebeautyofficial and Gel stick from  @bbluntindia .

🌸Wax Stick - I chose the Moxie one as this used a plant based wax which I prefer. As shared above its effective in settling the flyaway and very convenient to use. The results last a decent amount of time. My problem with this the little residue it leaves. You feel like washing the hair after this however that passes away by next day or if you comb through. Washing it off is  easy with a strong shampoo. Might not get off completely with a gentle one. Also the packaging is fragile. Mine broke after falling down just once (will share more in stories)

🌸 Gel Stick - This one is from bblunt and adds a great shine. Hold pretty decent for few hours. You can increase the quantity used for a longer hold. It just feels like a light Gel on the hair and leaves no residue and washing this off is very easy. This definitely gives a sleek look. The only problem with this is the hair it pulls. Almost on every application so you need to be very careful. Apart from that I absolutely love this. I end using this one most number of times. 

any other question ? Please ask in the comments .

#waxstick #gelstick #frizzyhair #flyaways #frizzyhairfix #babyhairsonfleek #frizzyhairproblems #frizzyhairsolution #curlyhaircare
